{"lemma":"سَلِيخَةٍ","slug":"سَلِيخَةٍ","root":"س.ل.خ","root_slug":"س-ل-خ","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ل-خ","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20401"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AE%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cassia, Cinnamomum cassia syn. Cinnamomum aromaticum"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root س ل خ (s l ḵ); a wanderwort with potential for a native Arabian Peninsula origin, Old South Arabian 𐩪𐩡𐩭𐩩 (s¹lḫt), Neo-Babylonian 𒋆𒃻𒇷𒄩𒌈 (/⁠šalīḫātu⁠/) (attested once as plural), Latin serichatum reported by Plin. nat. hist. XII 99. Classical Syriac ܡܫܠܚܬܐ (mǝšallaḥṯā) is apparently learnedly formed after Arabic, Classical Syriac ܣܠܝܟܗ (salīḵā) is only found in Bar Hebraeus and apparently a logogram of Arabic."},"ipa":["/sa.liː.xa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20401","headword_ar":"سَلِيخَةٌ","root":"slx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain perfume,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"odoriferous substance, resembling bark stripped off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and having"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEab","text_ar":"شُعَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forking projections"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  (assumed tropical:)  Of the [plants called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rimov","text_ar":"رِمْث"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earofaj","text_ar":"عَرْفَج"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such as has been stripped of what was good for pasture;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion that has in it nothing for pasture"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remaining;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting only of dry wood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) and of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Erfj","text_ar":"عرفج"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is thick, of what has become dried up."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oil of the fruit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"produce, of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAn","text_ar":"بَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bentree"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before it has been seasoned"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with aromatics:"},{"kind":"text","text":"when it has been seasoned with musk and [other] perfume, and then expressed, it is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano$uw$N","text_ar":"مَنْشُوشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and one says of it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nu$~a","text_ar":"نُشَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Offspring:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K, TA:) because it has been drawn out ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulixa","text_ar":"سُلِخَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuziEa","text_ar":"نُزِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":") from the belly of its mother. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","K","TA","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}